window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><i>LA Times</i> best-seller. Translated into seven languages. \"Kaplan is up there with the best.\" (Clive Cussler, author)</p> <p>In a last ditch effort to revive his career, washed-out Agent Ari Ben-Sion accepts a mission he never would have 30 years ago to smuggle a group of Jewish children out of the Damascus ghetto. Or so he thinks. </p> <p>In Damascus, a beautiful American photographer, Kim, seems to be falling in love with Ari, but she is asking too many questions. His communication equipment disappears. His contact never shows up. The operation is only hours away, and everything seems awry. </p> <p>Desperate to succeed, Ari might risk everything. Even his life. </p> <p>Soon to be a major motion picture.</p>"; 
